parameters: Karin: "Wahh...! What's with this forest maze?!"

I feel like we've been going around in circles for a while
now. It's as if we're being made to dance in the palm of the
trees...

Now that I think about it... I remember what Master said.
Last month, she created a "Labyrinth of Bewilderment" inside
the Forest of Spirits to prevent intruders...
What?! That's terrible! Is this maze that thing?

What should we do... Even if we wanted to go back, we've
wandered so much that we might not be able to find our way
back, right?

It's troubling... I thought it would be fine since I used to
live in this forest... Maybe it would have been better to
ask Master to come with us after all...

Karin: "Wahh... I don't have the energy to go back to Edo
after coming this far..."

We walked quite a bit to get past the checkpoint and come
here... If we keep wandering aimlessly, we'll just keep
losing strength. We have no choice but to make this place
our lodging and stay the night.

That's right. Then I'll go gather some firewood for the
campfire.
--Karin and the others began preparing for the campfire.

It was good that I brought extra food, thinking about what
might happen if we got stranded in the mountains.

Yeah. Somehow, eating meat around a campfire in the midst of
nature at night strangely stirs up emotions.

I've been living a nomadic life ever since I became a demon,
so it reminds me of old times...

Karin: "Um... Momiji... There's been a lot happening since
we left the pleasure district, and I haven't had the chance
to ask, but could you tell us in detail about what happened
in the Wind Demon Clan's village?"
Momiji: "...About the Wind Demon Clan's village?"

Since we heard that blue demon was Wind Demon Kotaro in the
last battle, we must know about our enemy. I'm also
interested.

I've always wanted to know why the survivors of the Wind
Demon Clan became demons... about my father and mother who
lived in the village... but...

But... I was afraid that learning the truth would shatter
everything I've known until now... I was too scared to ask.
But now, I really want to know. Especially since Kotaro told
me my father is dead... I want to know even more.

Momiji: "Is that okay with you, Karin-chan? Knowing about
the past isn't always a good thing. It might bring you
pain..."

Karin: "I'm prepared. Please tell me everything you know,
Momiji! About what happened in the Wind Demon Clan's village
over a hundred years ago--"

Momiji: "...Alright. Then I will tell you both. To be
precise, it was 123 years ago, what happened in the Wind
Demon Clan's village..."

...And after some time, my father joined Gyoun as a comrade,
albeit with hesitation, and the remnants of the Wind Demon
Clan who had become demons continued to kill people while
hiding in the shadows.
So that's what they call the Eight Grudge War Demons...

Yes. But I hated it and eventually fled from my father and
their group. However... The impulse to eat humans that had
been ingrained over many years was not something that could
easily be resisted... until I met Lady Masaki--
...So you met Masaki-chan here in this Forest of Spirits.

Yes. The pure and clear air here weakened my demonic
power... And thanks to Master's detoxification technique, or
rather her demon-purging technique, my urge to eat humans
gradually decreased over the years.

...Why did you leave this forest and live in the pleasure
district?

I felt somewhat guilty for always being under Master's
care... So I decided to live in the pleasure district.
Whenever I absolutely had to eat humans, I would feed on the
corpses of courtesans who had died from illness.

...I see. So that was your journey from the Wind Demon
Clan's village to the pleasure district.

It's been a long story, but that's what happened until I met
all of you. The silence of the night makes it easier for
people to talk...

It must have been tough after the Wind Demon Clan's village
was destroyed, Momiji-san...

If you were once with Gyoun as one of the War Demons, do you
not know his purpose, Lady Momiji?

I never killed people and wasn't very cooperative. I only
saw him at meetings held every few years... However, Gyoun
did advocate for demons to kill many humans without being
noticed, beyond just satisfying their hunger.

...! (Could that one-eyed demon who attacked Yugiri Village
be one of them?)

The souls of humans who die with resentment or grief become
spirits known as "Grudge." Gyoun mentioned that he needed
many of these spiritual sacrifices. I don't know why he's
collecting them.

Grudge...? Something like a soul filled with resentment...
What on earth are they planning to do with them?

...We won't know unless we ask Gyoun and Kotaro directly
when we confront them someday... For that, we first need to
get our hands on the demon-slaying sacred treasures located
here.

That's right. The night has grown late; let's sleep here for
tonight.

If we can get out of this forest maze, we should find it
soon. Let's give it our all again tomorrow. Good night--

--Karin, Yugiri, and Momiji fell asleep in front of the
campfire...
Yawn... The birds are chirping... Is it already... morning?
...You're awake, Karin? You were sleeping soundly.

Good morning, Karin-chan. You must have been tired; you
slept so deeply.

Huh, everyone's already up? I feel a bit embarrassed for
oversleeping like this... Ahaha...

Lady Momiji, recalling last night's conversation, I'm
curious... If eating the flesh of a demon turns one into a
demon, what would happen if someone ate your flesh?

In that case, they wouldn't become a demon. It seems that
only the flesh of what is called a "True Demon" can turn
someone into a demon... It's like how children inherit the
abilities of a demon, but grandchildren do not inherit
anything... That's how it works.
(I see... So mass-producing demons is difficult...)

Thank you for telling us, Lady Momiji. Now, let's break
through the Forest of Illusions today.
...! Wait! I sense the presence of some beast nearby!

--Nyahaha! So you were indeed stuck in the maze of
illusions?

My apologies for forgetting to mention it. Beyond here is my
temple... or rather my home territory. When I'm away, I've
set up a magical barrier to prevent easy entry because
things are rather dangerous now, aren't they?
Aww... You should have told us that beforehand...
This is troubling, Lady Masaki. We're all exhausted...

I'm truly sorry about that. I'll remove the barrier now.
There--!
--Masaki formed a seal and lifted the barrier!
